Coffee Syrup.
Take one kg of coffee, roast and grind it, then place it in a coated terracotta pot.
Pour 2 liters of boiling water over it, mix well with a spatula,
seal it tightly, and let it sit in a warm place for a day.
Afterward, strain the mixture. For every part of this infusion,
add two parts of virgin syrup. Then, place it on gentle heat and let it
reach a temperature of 32 degrees.
